name: San Juaquin Kit Fox
overview: Kit foxes are mostly active during nights. Kit foxes live under dens made by natural shelter or man made shelter. They use these shelters to protect there young and protect themselves from predators. They tend to change dens often going through about 25 dens a year. Kit foxes eat other small animals. They eat from small rodents, black hares, Kit foxes primarily eat rodents and other small animals, including black-tailed hares, desert cottontails, mice, kangaroo rats, squirrels, birds and lizards.
habitat: The Kit Fox is located the San Joaquin Valley. They live in dens.They also live in man made structures such as concrete abandoned structures.
